<text id="05-examples" title="Strangler-Fig Migration Playbook (Vendor Delivery) Worked Example" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="700" depth="essential">
  <summary>Worked example showing the methodology applied end-to-end, with a trace through the rules and the final spec artefact.</summary>

  <section title="Trace">
    <p>Vendor onboards a 60-route legacy monolith. `scripts/score-slices.py` produces the scoring table. First-3 selection follows r1 (low coupling first).</p>
  </section>

  <section title="Final artefact">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "slice_scoring_table": [
    {
      "slice_id": "S1",
      "route": "GET /api/health",
      "coupling_depth": 1,
      "traffic_risk": 1,
      "business_priority": 1,
      "selection_order": 1
    },
    {
      "slice_id": "S2",
      "route": "GET /api/products/recs",
      "coupling_depth": 2,
      "traffic_risk": 2,
      "business_priority": 4,
      "selection_order": 2
    },
    {
      "slice_id": "S3",
      "route": "GET /api/users/profile",
      "coupling_depth": 2,
      "traffic_risk": 3,
      "business_priority": 3,
      "selection_order": 3
    },
    {
      "slice_id": "S4",
      "route": "POST /api/checkout",
      "coupling_depth": 5,
      "traffic_risk": 5,
      "business_priority": 5,
      "selection_order": "defer"
    }
  ],
  "parity_burn_in_record": {
    "slice_id": "S2",
    "window_start": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z",
    "window_end": "2026-05-23T00:00:00Z",
    "duration_hours": 168,
    "error_rate_delta_percent": 1.2,
    "p99_latency_delta_percent": 3.5
  }
}
]]></code>
  </section>

  <section title="Rule trace">
    <list>
      <item>r1 satisfied: first slice coupling_depth=1.</item>
      <item>r2 satisfied: burn-in=168h with parity ±10%.</item>
      <item>r3 satisfied: kill-switch tested 5 days before cutover.</item>
      <item>r4 satisfied: dual-write window has termination date.</item>
    </list>
  </section>
</text>
